      "completenessGrade": "FULL",
      "sourceSnippet": "A steroidal MRA should be used for treatment of heart failure, hyperaldosteronism, or refractory hypertension, but may cause hyperkalemia or a reversible decline in glomerular filtration, particularly among patients with a low eGFR. the use of steroidal MRA also increases the risk of hyperkalemia (by 2- to 3-fold) and of AKI (approximately 2-fold)",
