      "sourceSnippet": "Hyperkalemia was the most common adverse event with finerenone. Serum potassium should be monitored after initiation of a nonsteroidal MRA and dose adjusted accordingly. Finerenone and esaxerenone are nonsteroidal MRA that are more selective for mineralocorticoid receptors, with similar reductions in albuminuria as steroidal MRA but a lower risk of hyperkalemia.",
